      "message": "I\u0027m suggesting that you don\u0027t really _need_ to add reset() methods to most types.  If you want to reset an object you can always just destruct it and use placement new to reconstruct it again.\n\n$ cat foo.cc\n#include \u003cnew\u003e\n#include \u003cstdio.h\u003e\n\ntemplate \u003ctypename K, typename V\u003e\nstruct Map {\n     Map() { printf(\"hello\\n\"); }\n    ~Map() { printf(\"bye\\n\"); }\n};\n\nint main(void) {\n    using M \u003d Map\u003cint,float\u003e;\n\n    M map;\n    map.~M();\n    new (\u0026map) M;\n\n    return 0;\n}\n\n$ clang++ -std\u003dc++11 foo.cc \u0026\u0026 ./a.out\nhello\nbye\nhello\nbye",
